Disney officials consulted Chinese feng shui experts before building Hong Kong Disneyland, adjusting the park's orientation and layout.
The groundbreaking and opening dates were chosen based on feng shui principles.
Despite expectations of boosting tourism, concerns remain about the economic impact.
The park aims to attract visitors from mainland China, with plans to enhance transportation and infrastructure.
Issues of overcrowding and ticket sales have arisen, prompting adjustments in operations.
Overall, Hong Kong Disneyland's opening signifies a new chapter in the city's tourism industry, emphasizing family-friendly attractions and government support for a successful launch.
